INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7239, 12, '2013-11-21 17:30:20', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Leverage the latest tools / Always adding new tools</h3>\r\n<p>could be about mapping tools, technology ect...</p>\r\n<h3>Links off line and online marketing strats</h3>\r\n<p>need a cohesive marketing strategy that links online and offline channels</p>\r\n<h3>Socially active </h3>\r\n<p>use social media to understand more about consumer patterns</p>\r\n<h3>Standard site processes</h3>\r\n<p>- standardize site finding / store development pipeline with best practice business processes</p>\r\n<h3>Exploring new dev solutions</h3>\r\n<p>value store development solutions the same way you would other industry solutions (accounting, supply chain, HR, manufacturing, etc.)</p>\r\n<h3>Do their research</h3>\r\n<p>-market research (target areas, customers, and competitors)</p>\r\n<h3>Approaches things locally </h3>\r\n<p>-work with local partner</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Habit 1 - "Be Proactive"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Habit 2 - Begin with the </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '7 Habits Of Highly Effective Retailers In China', 0, '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-11-21 17:30:20', '2013-11-21 09:30:20', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=7239', 0, 'post', '', 0, '4427'); 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7157, 88902, '2013-11-28 12:30:21', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<p>As emerging markets continue to grow along with disposable incomes in those regions, many investors are still looking to expand to the Asia-Pacific region.  However, original strategy and business models in Europe and American markets don\'t always work well in their efforts to globalize. Here are 3 basic concerns to be "globalized", both globalization and localization, in the blue sea.</p>\r\n<p>1. Do as Romans do!</p>\r\n<p>Yes! We understand how successful your business model run based on accumulated years of experiences in other market, but are you 100% sure that it works the same way in countries of people speaking different language and behaving unpredictably due to local customs?</p>\r\n<p>Some analysts consider that it might be the reason that Wal-Mart and Carrefour withdraw from Japan and Korea market, because they were not fully aware of the customer behaviors. Though buying what you need is the major shopping reason, Korea customers still enjoy the feeling of window shopping as a leisure activity. Locating stores outside downtown can have the price advantage by cheaper rent, but many target customers in Japan care about immediate fresh foods, not willing to stock all in home refrigerator weekly, even with less spending.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2. Language translation only?</p>\r\n<p>Could local target consumers understand what you want to reveal from the product bordures, websites, or commercials? You may receive customer complaints from different countries from time to time, about offended by the same commercials or expressions used in those native language speaking ones. Therefore, it is very important to be aware of how local consumers really look, so translating all into local language is not enough at all. For example, eBay insisted to copy all the platform structure as its strategy oversea, but it didn\'t work out the same way in Asia market. You will never know whether local consumers might get annoyed by all commercial bombings, and begin to reject being one of the global brand colonies.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3. Culture difference</p>\r\n<p>The "Glocalization" concept is discussed more and more because all these issues happen in global market, which means that global localization must integrate both. Certain products sold well in office building areas in your country might not succeed in similar kind of areas in Asia, caused by the varied working population flowing trend daily in weekdays or weekends. It is naive to think that local consumers will swarm like bees after establishing a website with local language and using the same commercials and promotions. They would appreciate products with cultural meanings and stories more. How to localize your brand and blend it into customers\' everyday life in local market is a crucial concern an enterprise should take very seriously.</p>', '3 basic Concerns to "Glocalizing" for your brand', 0, '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-11-28 12:30:21', '2013-11-28 04:30:21', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=7157', 0, 'post', '', 0, '4427'); 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7311, 88899, '2013-12-12 13:03:30', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<p>POI is a point feature on a map. In business terminology it could represent a retail chain’s spatial distribution. Now we use internet map very often for navigation, location search, or analysis purpose.</p>\r\n<p>This article is going to tell how POI data is made</p>\r\n<p>Generally, map vendor is the most possible role to generate point of interest data. They assign surveyor to the street and record what they see the brand name, address, in which floor and its location information, such as coordinate (X,Y) message from GPS device. It is very traditional method and good contribution work. However, it costs a lot.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here getchee would like to share a commonly method to generate specific POI in business world.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 1</strong> - Select your target brands.<span style="font-size: small;"> </span></h3>\r\n<p>xxxxxxxxx</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 2</strong> - Go visit the brands official website</h3>\r\n<p>and find its branch/door list webpage</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 3</strong> - Find and collect important data.</h3>\r\n<p>copy and make a list with address and important messages, such as branch name, telephone, open day/hour and channel type</p>\r\n<p>xxxxxxxxxxx</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 4</strong> - Clean the information</h3>\r\n<p>clean the address and make it looks like “door #, street name, district name, city name, province/state name, zip code” format, which could increase the geocoding accuracy</p>\r\n<p>xxxxxxxxxxx</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 5</strong> - Map the POI.</h3>\r\n<p>if you are a programmer, there are several free map API you could apply to code a batch auto geocode machine. Otherwise put one address to internet map and get its x, y coordinates manually</p>\r\n<p>xxxxxxxxxx</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 6</strong> - Generate a database</h3>\r\n<p>Once you have the coordinates information, use GIS software to generate spatial dataset, such as ESRI (shapefile), Autodesk, Mapinfo and so on.  Job done</p>\r\n<p> xxxxxxxxx</p>\r\n<p>Below graph describe more detail progress of a standard POI generation. You might take a look.</p>\r\n<p>[Blog06_geocoding_workflow.png]</p>', 'How POI Data Made - In 6 Steps', 0, '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-12-12 13:03:30', '2013-12-12 05:03:30', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=7311', 0, 'post', '', 0, '4427'); 
